                            A N T   H E A D S

                                 Solution

                                  DAY 1

Start by gathering all the information you can from Biff and Dusty, unless
you already know what's going on.  Go to the gas station and get acquanted
with Elmer.  Then take a trip to KBUG.  Dusty then tells you about the
aftermath of the last ant attack and gives you a gun and a Geiger counter.
Hang around until the afternoon and visit the platt university lab.  In
there you'll find little Billy and his scheptical dad. Ignore the old man
and listen to all Billy's advice. For some further info pop in on Ida the
fortune teller.  Get home for around eight and you'll be able to spend a
not so quiet evening with the ever amorous Jackie.


                                  DAY 2

Once again your first excursion should be to KBUG, where Dusty warns you
of the impending threat from the G-men.  After that go to the lab where
Billy has some more useful information for you.  You will have a run in
with Jackie at some stage, which will lead to a fight with her boyfriend.
At about one o'clock drive over to Neptune Hall where you'll find Billy
Bob acting even stranger than usual, if you count strange as a full set of
antennae and mandibles.  You've just met your first Ant head.  Whip out
your Colt .45 and shoot him where the antennae joins the head.  After the
transformation from Ant-head to Billy Bob you get one of the most vital
pieces of information in the game, a number.  Make a note of this, and
thats day two.


                                  DAY 3

Sat your alarm clock for nine o'clock. You should wake up with Jackie at
the door, who then wakes you up even further by becomming an Ant-head.
Shoot her head as before, and write down the number she gives you.  Plod
over to the ore plant and butter up the manager by selecting 'Crude
Remark' A.  Hop onto the train to M3 and dispose of the Ants you find
there.  Once you've massacared a few dozen Ants shimmy back to platt
laboratory for a meet with Billy.  He will give you some Pez (a sugary
sweet, which enables to tell if people are Ant-heads).  Try to arrive at
the Police station at around five o'clock, get knocked unconscious and put
in hospital.  When you regain consciousness, the nurse will give you the
location of the vault where the Ant-heads store the records of the
conversion process.  Then all you have to do is escape.


                                  DAY 4

Drop in at Elmore's.  When he turns into an Ant-head, shoot his head as
before and get the final number.  Once you have all three numbers go to
the Hospital, grab a wheelchair, and take a lift to the basement. Towards
the top-right of the floor is the morgue, recognise the four black slabs
and the grey safe inside.  Go up to the safe and enter the numbers in the
order you found them.  If you have done this correctly, you will
automatically collect the documents.  If you manage to escape from the
Hospital, lizard Breath finally wakes up to the threat of the ants, and
quite courteously puts you in charge of wiping them out.  The Queens nest
is near mine four, jump into a hole left by one of the Ants, and leave a
time-bomb.

