                            B A R B A R I A N

                                  Hints

THE PENDULUM: Go to the first spot on the screen when the pendulum swings
nearest to you, run your head off, jump at the last minute and pray.  Most
of the time it works.

You need a bow with the fire throwers.

At about what percentage do the fire throwers come in?  At about 50%.

THE SHIELD: you can't win without it.  It is two screens after the dragon.
What do I do with it?  You will need it later.  The situation for the
shield  be obvious, read the manual and you will see it.

Do the down commands before you reach a ladder.

STRATEGY: Have a good memory.  A couple of notes though.  Don't bother
with the tin man, he is just there to scare you.  When facing a QBert,
walk towards him, then when he makes his second jump, evade and strike.
Also, on the screen where the guy comes out from the floor, run towards
him and jump just after he shoots.  Then strike to destroy the guy
walking.  On qbert, run and flip over him.  He turns around and comes
back, but you easily out run him.

The easiest way to get the dragon is right after you enter that screen,
fire two arrows quickly and evade immediately, which means you need the
second bow.  Just flip over his fireball. You will need every arrow later
on, so save them.  When you reach the fire shooters you will wish you had
arrows.

The club guys are easy to do away with using the sword.

After the dragon comes the screen with the shield.  Then after climbing a
series of ladders you come to a series of wooden walkways with ugly guys
with clubs.  After this comes a screen with falling dagger traps and then
comes the pendulum.

Keep going up and to the right to see the pendulum.  You'll know you are
there when the screen changes to a reddish color.

To get the second bow, first I do away with the guard.  Next run and flip
onto the bow screen to miss the trap.  Then run to the bow, grab it and
immediately evade out of there.

To preload commands (because of programming delays, when fighting, some
leading is necessary) press run, jump, down all at once and it will follow
the order.

Use the mouse.  Much better control than joystick.

The Ironman is invincible.


