                             B L O O D W Y C H

                                   Hints

If your patient enough, a good way of starting is to recruit your way
through all of the chracsters, taking their belongings, and then dismissing
them. Yuo can now sell all weapons you don't want, to end up with about 200
coinage. You will also have a plentiful supply of food and keys, so
remember to have only one character carrying the keys to save on backpack
space.

The best combination of characters is to have two fighters at the front,
and two wizards at the back. It's difficult to say which colours are best,
since they all have spells which come in very useful.  The yellow Vivify
spell is probably best, but red spells such as Vitalise, fireball and
firebath tend to be most frequently used.  Note that the first time you use
the Vivify spell, you will need about 70 to 80 spell points if the
character casting the spell isn't yellow.

Any items you come across can be sold to any creature, so long as they're
not one of the characters you robbed at the beginning of the game.  You can
quite easily reach and maintain the maximum of 99 coinage this way.

As far as fighting goes, make sure you don't get trapped while using the
'hack and step back' method, only to realise that you haven't saved the
game for some time. Occasionally it is possible to worm your way out of
this situation by using the confuse and terror spells and talking to the
creature.  Keep boasting to it about how great you are, and then threaten
it. Every now and then the creature will turn and run, but unfortuanally
this is quite rare.

A good tip is the 'hiding behind the door technique'.  Stand to one side of
the wooden door with the creature on the other side and keep clicking on
the fight icon until the creature opens the diir.  Sometimes it is possible
to get a hit from both of your front characters and close the door before
the creature hits you.  If the creature then opens the door straight away,
you won't need to click on the fight icon again.  If there is a delay,
you'll probably have to keep hitting it.  If you've worried that one of
your characters is going to die, then lock the door usinf magelock, as it's
quite easy to make the mistake of locking the door open if you use a key.
With the door locked you can give your characters a rest, allowing them to
recuperate and be ready for the next fight.

